      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Replace torque converter case drive pulley shaft bearing"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Drive pulley shaft bearing removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "582_3.0_jpn_11035253_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove drive pulley shaft bearing (A) using bearing remover shaft, adjustable bearing remover 45-75 and sliding hammer weight."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Drive Pulley Shaft Bearing Mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "582_3.0_jpn_11035254_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Install a new bearing using the driver handle 15 x 135L and bearing driver attachment 52 x 55. Press-fit the bearing securely until it butts up against the case."
    }
  ],
